al trouble down the road. The indenture governing the notes includes an unu=
sual provision: After December 3=E2=80=94last Tuesday=E2=80=94note holders =
have the right to require the company to repurchase, for cash, all or a por=
tion of the debt, plus accrued and unpaid interest, which amounts to anothe=
r $4.7 million.

In its latest 10-Q filing, BuzzFeed said it expected to receive notices fro=
m
note holders on November 22, requiring it to pay the $124 million of princi=
pal plus accrued interest. The problem, of course, is that if that happens,=
 or happened=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s not yet clear whether it did=E2=80=94Buzz=
Feed doesn=E2=80=99t appear to have the money. The filing says BuzzFeed has=
 $54 million in cash as of September 30=E2=80=94which is not nothing, but c=
learly not $124 million.

