           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">BuzzFeed said it would try to =
either refinance the notes or negotiate a new deal with the note holders. B=
ut, the filing hastened to add, either or both of those efforts might fail,=
 resulting in an =E2=80=9Cevent of default.=E2=80=9D BuzzFeed =E2=80=9Cdoes=
 not have sufficient cash on hand or projected cash flows to fund the repay=
ment of the [n]otes,=E2=80=9D the company conceded. It also added, with con=
siderable understatement, that the =E2=80=9Cuncertainty=E2=80=9D regarding =
repayment could affect the volatility of the company=E2=80=99s stock. It ce=
rtainly would. (This is not investment advice.)<br/><br/>Not surprisingly, =
BuzzFeed has put everything on the table financially=E2=80=94from an attemp=
ted debt restructuring, to asset sales, to more layoffs. This is not a pret=
ty financial picture, which brings us to this admission in the filing: =E2=
=80=9CThese uncertainties raise substantial doubt about the Company=E2=80=
=99s
ability to continue as a going concern.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Part of this, of=
 course, was BuzzFeed=E2=80=99s own doing, a product of the SPAC deal, the =
note issuance, and the acquisitions of HuffPost and other entities like Com=
plex=E2=80=94to say nothing of its aggressive boom-time overexpansion. The =
company=E2=80=99s S.E.C. filing reminds us that it was founded by <b>Jonah =
Peretti</b> in 2006 as =E2=80=9Ca lab=E2=80=9D in New York=E2=80=99s Chinat=
own =E2=80=9Cexperimenting with how the Internet could change how content i=
s consumed, distributed, interacted with, and shared.=E2=80=9D Pretty grand=
iose aspirations. And, for a time, it seemed like the experiment might work=
=2E BuzzFeed raised nearly $500 million=
 from many intelligent investors at a=20=
now-<i>preposterous</i> $1.7 billion valuation.<br/><br/>But these days, it=
=E2=80=99s the losses that are generating BuzzFeed=E2=80=99s buzz as much a=
s the quizzes and food videos. For the nine months ended September 30, the =
company generated revenue of $156 million and losses from operations of $21=
=2E4
million. It also generated the dreaded =E2=80=9Cadjusted EBITDA=E2=80=9D of=
 nearly $2 million (actually not much, all things considered, especially wi=
th $119 million of debt). I wouldn=E2=80=99t count Peretti out=E2=80=94he=
=E2=80=99s pulled many digital rabbits out of his hat over the years. But I=
=E2=80=99m not sure how he deals with his current problems short of concedi=
ng a large chunk of his company to the holders of those notes. Could it be =
change-of-control time at BuzzFeed? Stay tuned. <br/><br/><i>And now, some =
notes on the M&amp;A landscape and Soto-nomics=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/></p><u=
