x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Sotheby=E2=80=99s d=
ecision to shrink the profitable company suggests the goal may be to genera=
te more cash flow. One supporting clue lies in the documents filed with Com=
panies House in the U.K. for Sotheby=E2=80=99s Holdings UK Limited, which r=
eveal that the firm has a dual-class share structure. The preferred shares =
in the company pay an 11 percent dividend. If ADQ received those preferred =
shares for its investment, the payout would be an additional $100 million e=
ach year. <br/><br/>The additional dividend obviously presents a problem fo=
r Drahi, who ostensibly does not want to rely solely on the potential rise =
in value of his equity in the company. (Sotheby=E2=80=99s C.E.O. <b>Charlie=
 Stewart</b> <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRn=
VDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUdDltV1BTeFVfdjVnQWN4VFR3Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9=
3d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRzLWN1bHR1cmUvZmluZS1hcnQvYXJ0LW1hcmtldC1zb3RoZWJ5cy1wcm=
9ibGVtcy02ZmE1NTAwOT91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyO=
DEyJTJGMTElMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVS=
UyslMjgxMiUyRjExJTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV=
0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLC=
JpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwMTQxODZ9/fbf10e71=
8bbb7f200695a807bb2463149af6fd85ee3c5e034882bcd6af8e89ef" style=3D"color:#d=
40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">told</a></u> <i>=
The</i> <i>Wall Street Journal</i> earlier this year that none of the previ=
ous dividends have left its network of holding companies. Others point out =
that Drahi focuses on tax management and nesting structures, which may expl=
ain why the ultimate holding company is located in Luxembourg.) Management =
does have the option to make a payment in kind if Sotheby=E2=80=99s lacks t=
he cash to pay ADQ=E2=80=99S 11 percent dividend. That would likely require=
 the company to give ADQ additional shares, a move that could easily tip th=
e balance of ownership=E2=80=94and control=E2=80=94away from Drahi. <br/><b=
r/>No one thinks Drahi will let go of the company easily, however. Thus, he=
 may be buying time by cutting staff while hoping the art market rebounds. =
Sales in Miami and in New York last month <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.=
news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUdDltV1BTeFVfdjVnQWN4VF=
R3Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvbmV3LXlvcmstZmFsbC1hcnQtYXVjdGlvb=
nMtcmV2aWV3Lz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODEyJTJG=
MTElMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjg=
xMiUyRjExJTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3=
VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlc=
m5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjE5OTQ4NDJ9/df3a28fb1eb9dd9=
69776544479f65b74f78423510fbd7d0a8e8b3a99398374bc" style=3D"color:#d40000;t=
ext-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">suggest</a></u> that th=
e art market has turned a corner, or at least that it=E2=80=99s found the b=
ottom, which means Sotheby=E2=80=99s could ride the next wave of the cycle =
back to the point where Drahi can sell for the $5 billion valuation he once=
 allegedly coveted, benefitting both himself and his partner. And from what=
 I can tell, most of this week=E2=80=99s layoffs are in departments that ar=
e not likely to move the needle in the next wave. <br/><br/>We=E2=80=99re n=
ot hearing of many departures from contemporary art, for example. And the w=
ay the auction business works, Sotheby=E2=80=99s thinning the ranks of spec=
ialists doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily put it in a less competitive position. =
Even after the growth of Phillips and the brightening prospects of Bonhams,=
 the auction world remains a duopoly. On any big estate or consignment of p=
roperty,
sellers will always want to get a competitive bid from the other side.<br/>=
<br/>As we saw with the <b>Sydell Miller </b>estate, the power of Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s platform can be activated by a small, well-organized team workin=
g for the consignor. This has been done before. In 2010, Phillips partnered=
 with <b>Philippe S=C3=A9galot</b> to mount the $117 million Carte Blanche =
sale. S=C3=A9galot, a former Christie=E2=80=99s head of contemporary art, d=
id most of the work=E2=80=94assembling the property, cultivating the bidder=
s, and even manning the phones at the sale. For one night, he was a one-man=
 contemporary art department=E2=80=A6 and the sale was a rousing success. W=
ith the army of former auction house specialists now freelancing as art adv=
isors and Sotheby=E2=80=99s sterling name, the company could easily run the=
se sorts of asset-light auctions in its new sale rooms at the Breuer on Mad=
ison Avenue. <br/><br/>A year ago, Stewart attended <u><a href=3D"https://e=
mail.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUdDltV1BTeFVf=
djVnQWN4VFR3Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9nYWdvc2lhbi5jb20vZXhoaWJpdGlvbnMvMjA=
yMy9hLWZvcmVpZ25lci1jYWxsZWQtcGljYXNzby1jdXJhdGVkLWJ5LWFubmllLWNvaGVuLXNvbG=
FsLWFuZC12ZXJhbmUtdGFzc2VhdS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQ=
kVSUyslMjgxMiUyRjExJTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1EcnkrUG93ZGVyKy0rU1VC=
U0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTIlMkYxMSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25=
cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYW=
JkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDE0MTg4f=
Q/eb5f6685314cc50fe8d00f862e3d69b61fb73968e0d0b6cf64d6b5c77d9d4685" style=
=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">Gago=
sian gallery=E2=80=99s show</a></u> of <b>Picasso </b>works, curated by wri=
ter <b>Annie Cohen-Solal</b>, and came away deeply impressed and excited by=
 the prospect of mounting his own museum-quality shows. He wondered aloud t=
o several of his staff what it would take, not seeming to understand that a=
ll his team lacked were the funds=E2=80=94and time=E2=80=94to mount such a =
show, let alone several of them a year. A person familiar with the planning=
 of the Gagosian show told me that the insurance fees on the eight-figure p=
aintings on loan were not for the weak of heart.<br/><br/>But with a showca=
se like the Breuer building, where
many decades of museum shows generated lines around the block, Sotheby=E2=
=80=99s ought to have a major draw for its stable of corporate sponsors to =
offset the expense. In other words, there=E2=80=99s no obvious reason why S=
otheby=E2=80=99s cannot thrive with a reduced focus on fine art.  <br/><br/=
>At this moment, the auction houses have never had such different business =
strategies. The restructuring at Sotheby=E2=80=99s this month recognizes th=
eir diverging paths. That said, Sotheby=E2=80=99s new strategy will require=
 the kind of flawless execution that proved elusive in Tuesday=E2=80=99s la=
yoffs. <br/></td>
